<HEADLINE>
<P>
CSUN QUAKE REPAIRS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Your report on earthquake recovery (July 17) correctly stresses the amount 
of work yet to do. However, because repair work at Cal State Northridge has 
continued around the clock this summer, conditions on campus will be much 
better this fall than last spring. 
</P>
<P>
 Sections of several major permanent classroom buildings have been repaired and 
will house classes. The core of the Oviatt Library building will reopen, 
allowing access to its vast book collection and study spaces. Most classes and 
all labs will take place on campus rather than off. Student housing has been 
strengthened and will reopen. And important new buildings will open for the 
first time. 
</P>
<P>
 Although major repair work will continue on campus as throughout Los Angeles, 
the work that has been done so far will greatly improve classroom and study 
conditions at Northridge this fall. 
</P>
<P>
 BRUCE ERICKSON 
</P>
<P>
 Director, Public Relations 
</P>
<P>
 Cal State Northridge 
</P>
</TEXT>
