<HEADLINE>
<P>
REPRESENTATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I found Andrew Reding's analysis of the single-transferable-vote system quite 
interesting but I was disturbed by the philosophy behind it ("Making Every Vote 
Really Count," Commentary, July 17). While on the one hand Reding asserts that 
"There is no presumption that members of a given ethnic group will always want 
to vote on the basis of their ethnicity," he concludes that the objective is 
"(to achieve) a Congress and state legislatures that look like America. . . ." 
</P>
<P>
 I for one would prefer legislators who think like America. What they look like 
seems to me to be irrelevant. 
</P>
<P>
 DAVID C. BLOXHAM 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach 
</P>
