<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL NOTES: FULLERTON'S NOE, PARK QUALIFY FOR MATCH PLAY AT USGA JUNIOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Terry Noe and Jin Park, both of Fullerton, qualified Wednesday for match play 
in the USGA Junior Amateur Championships at Echo Lake Country Club in 
Westfield, N.J. 
</P>
<P>
 Noe shot 73 for a two-round total of 143, four strokes behind leader Michael 
Henderson of Raleigh, N.C., who shot a 69 to go with an opening 70. Park had 75 
for a 146 total, seven under the cut at 153. Jimmy Lee of Irvine finished at 
155. 
</P>
<P>
 The tournament, for players under the age of 18, switches to match play today. 
The semifinals and final are scheduled Saturday. Tiger Woods won the title the 
last three years. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Jenny Lee of Fullerton was in fifth place after shooting a par 71 in the 
second round of the American Junior Golf Assn. Betsy Rawls Girls' National 
Championship at the Du Pont Country Club in Wilmington, Del. 
</P>
<P>
 Lee, at 147, is five strokes behind the leader Grace Park of Phoenix. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Jeffrey McGraw of Fullerton shot par 72, then won a five-hole playoff for 
medalist honors in a qualifier in the 15-16 division of the American Junior 
Golf Assn. Boys' Junior at Bear Creek Golf Resort in Dallas. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Matt Brady of Villa Park High has signed a letter of intent to play baseball 
at Cal Poly San Luis Obispo. 
</P>
<P>
 Brady, a pitcher and outfielder, was 6-3 with a 2.15 earned-run average. He 
also hit .453 with four home runs and 23 runs batted in. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Bullfrogs announced a two-for-one ticket offer for the two remaining 
Roller Hockey International games at The Pond of Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
 Friday, Anaheim will play host to Las Vegas and the Bullfrogs' home schedule 
concludes Aug. 2 with fan appreciation night and a game against Vancouver. Both 
games begin at 7:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets ranging from $8-$50 are available at the Pond of Anaheim or 
TicketMaster outlets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
