VALLEY RANGERS WIN OPENER, 6-1 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brad Coukos pitched a five-hitter, leading the Valley Rangers to a 6-1 
first-round victory in the double-elimination Connie Mack state playoffs 
Wednesday at Fullerton College. 
</P>
<P>
 The Valley Rangers (25-2), a Glendale-based team that includes many of the 
area's top high school players, faces Long Beach Ocean View today at 5 p.m. at 
Fullerton College. 
</P>
<P>
 Coukos, who pitched at College of the Canyons last spring, struck out five and 
walked one. Saugus High's Brandon Hernandez was one of three Rangers with two 
hits. 
</P>
