<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: SAUGUS TO SCRAP SPORTSMAN RACING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Saugus Speedway announced plans Wednesday to eliminate the Sportsman Division 
during the 1995 racing season because of increasing costs and dwindling 
participation. 
</P>
<P>
 Instead, the Late Model Division will be created and will take over as the 
elite division at Saugus. The Late Model Division will be formed from the 
current Pro Stock Division but will feature late-model bodies on a stock 
chassis, according to Ray Wilkings, track general manager. 
</P>
<P>
 "The Sportsman Division is suffering from cost escalation and the car count is 
graphic evidence of this," Wilkings said. 
</P>
<P>
 In the new division, the bodies of the cars, all from 1990 or later, will be 
similar to those on the NASCAR Southwest and Northwest tours. Engines will 
remain stock. 
</P>
<P>
 A Pure Stock Division also will be established for entry-level drivers. The 
division will consist of American-made passenger cars with little modification 
except for safety-related equipment. The Grand American Modified, Street Stock 
and Mini-Stock divisions will return for 1995, Wilkings said. Golf 
</P>
<P>
 Chad Wright of Ventura fired consecutive six-under 66s to win the Camarillo 
City Junior championship in a runaway at Camarillo Springs Golf Course. 
</P>
<P>
 Wright, an 18-year-old sophomore at USC, won by 25 shots over Tim Wren and 
Brent Hendon, both of Oxnard, who tied for second at 157. Jeff Nichwander of 
Camarillo was third at 161. 
</P>
<P>
 In the 14-15 age group, Brian Kang of Westlake Village shot 80 to edge Dusty 
Morton of Ventura by one shot. 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Anderson of Ventura and Ojai's Jeff Coburn and Mike Hewitt finished in a 
three-way tie for first in the 13-and-under division at 82. 
</P>
<P>
 Julia Kaopua of Oxnard won the girls' division with a 79. The next Ventura 
County Junior Golf Assn. event is scheduled for today at 1 p.m. at Sunset Hills 
Country Club in Thousand Oaks. Wrestling 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark College will sponsor a clinic at the school gymnasium Saturday from 8 
a.m. to 5 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The clinic will feature instruction from three former college standouts: Gerry 
Abas and Serge Mezheritsky of Fresno State and Neal Mason of Cal Poly San Luis 
Obispo. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: 805-378-1457. Motor Sports 
</P>
<P>
 Entries are being accepted for the annual Ventura County Fair demolition derby 
Aug. 19. 
</P>
<P>
 Contestants will drive station wagons and luxury cars that have seen better 
days.  
</P>
<P>
 Information: 805-656-1122. Miscellany 
</P>
<P>
 Low-cost high school sports physicals and free immunization will be offered at 
the Glendale Adventist Hospital, 1509 Wilson Terrace, on Aug. 21 and Aug. 28, 
from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: 818-409-8100. 
</P>
