<HEADLINE>
<P>
LAWNDALE TAKING APPLICATIONS FOR TAX EXEMPTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON GARCIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lawndale officials are accepting applications for exemptions to the city's new 
utility tax. 
</P>
<P>
 The 5.5% tax approved June 16 excluded senior citizens and low-income or 
disabled residents. But residents who qualify must apply for the exemption, 
said Thomas A. Devereux, director of community services for the city. 
</P>
<P>
 Although there is no deadline for filing, the higher rates will begin to 
appear on residents' bills after Monday. Residents who file for exemption after 
the new rates go into effect will be eligible for a refund, Devereux said. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications may be picked up at the City Hall finance department. 
Information: (310) 970-2100, Ext. 124. JON GARCIA 
</P>
</TEXT>
