<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL NEWS: POLICE DEPARTMENT GETS 3% PAY INCREASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF KASS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sworn officers and other Police Department workers will receive 3% pay raises 
under a new contract approved Tuesday night by the City Council. 
</P>
<P>
 The council imposed the one-year contract after failing to reach an agreement 
with the 31-member Police Officers Assn. after more than a year of 
negotiations. Other municipal employees received 3% pay raises early this 
month. 
</P>
<P>
 Detective Dave Blitz, head of the association, said he was disappointed with 
the contract. Police officers were hoping for raises of 5% to 6%, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Officer's salaries will range from $34,800 to $43,600 under the new contract. 
JEFF KASS 
</P>
</TEXT>
