<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: GLENDORA; POLICE SEEK VOLUNTEERS FOR AUXILIARY PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Glendora Police Department is looking for senior citizens and other 
residents to donate their time as police auxiliary volunteers. 
</P>
<P>
 Volunteer officers will perform of variety of duties at the police station and 
in the community. They might be asked to fingerprint job applicants, direct 
traffic, answer telephones, take reports, inventory property, issue bicycle and 
dog licenses, and participate in safety programs and public appearances. 
</P>
<P>
 Interested applicants must be at least 21 years old, in good health and 
possess good moral character.  
</P>
<P>
 Applications will be accepted through Aug. 8 at the Glendora Police station, 
150 S. Glendora Ave. For more information, contact Paul Sheldon at (818) 
914-8278. 
</P>
</TEXT>
