<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: ANGELES FOREST; PUBLIC INPUT SOUGHT ON LONG-TERM POLICY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Angeles National Forest officials will hold a public meeting on Monday to 
solicit public comment on the development of long-term policy plans. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mt. Baldy District meeting, from 6 to 9 p.m. at Glendora City Hall, will 
be part of a series. The public can talk about recent cutbacks that have caused 
the closure of several recreational areas in the forest, or any other aspect of 
forest management. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (818) 574-1613. 
</P>
