<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: GLENDORA; AUTO CLUB MERGES 2 UNITS AT NEW OFFICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Automobile Club of Southern California has opened a new district office in 
Glendora.The office primarily serves members living in the East San Gabriel 
Valley, replacing the former Auto Club offices in Azusa and Covina. 
</P>
<P>
 The new facility offers a travel agency, insurance sales and claims 
adjustment, and the usual maps, tour books, fee-free travelers checks and help 
with motor vehicle registration and traffic citations. 
</P>
<P>
 The Glendora office is at 1301 Grand Ave. Business hours are 9 a.m. to 5 p.m., 
Monday through Friday. In addition, the Auto Club's Chino and Arcadia offices 
are now open Saturdays from 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (818) 963-8531. 
</P>
