<HEADLINE>
<P>
ARTIE GLENN; BASS PLAYER'S SONG BECAME PRESLEY HIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Artie Glenn, 79, whose song "Crying in the Chapel" became a hit for Elvis 
Presley and several other recording artists.Glenn played bass with bands and 
toured the South and Midwest in the 1950s and '60s. Presley released his 
version of "Chapel" in 1965 and the single sold more than 500,000 copies and 
reached the top five on the charts. Among the bands Glenn played with were the 
Dixielanders and the Westerners. Although he had not toured in many years, he 
never stopped composing. He was in the studio last weekend working on another 
song, said his wife, Foy. In Dallas on Monday of a heart attack. 
</P>
