<HEADLINE>
<P>
W. DORR LEGG; FOUNDER OF GAY SUPPORT GROUP ONE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 W. Dorr Legg, 89, founder of ONE, Inc., among the oldest gay and lesbian 
support organizations in the country. The group, with headquarters on Country 
Club Drive in West Los Angeles, offers therapy, counseling and referrals to the 
gay community.It also provides educational and job placement programs, one of a 
very few umbrella organizations for gays when it first started in the early 
1950s. When Legg and others wanted to publicize ONE by starting a national 
magazine, they had to take the Postal Service to court because the U.S. mail 
refused to handle it because of content. Legg was a landscape architect and 
musician who had never been politically active until he founded ONE. In Los 
Angeles on Tuesday. 
</P>
