<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRAZILIAN CRAWLS BACK TO GIRLFRIEND -- LITERALLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A love-struck Brazilian artist, distraught over the breakup of a four-year 
relationship with his girlfriend, walked nine miles on his knees in a bid to 
win back her love. 
</P>
<P>
 Shuffling along with pieces of car tire tied to his kneecaps and cheered on by 
motorists and passersby, 21-year-old Marcio da Silva took 14 hours to complete 
his marathon of love from Praia Grande to Santos on the Sao Paulo coast. 
</P>
<P>
 The gesture was in vain. When he arrived, exhausted, at her home, 19-year-old 
Katia de Nascimento had left to avoid seeing him. 
</P>
