<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHO RIDES THE BUS? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Even transit officials acknowledge that Californians have a love affair with 
their cars. The Metropolitan Transportation Authority's studies show that its 
most frequent bus passengers tend to be those without wheels of their own. 
</P>
<P>
 Ethnic minorities and low-income people make up a majority of the ridership. 
So do women -- according to the MTA, 57.3% of bus riders in Los Angeles County 
are female, compared to 53.4% of the county population. 
</P>
<P>
 Here's a look at some other demographics: HOUSEHOLD INCOME 
