ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAGUNA HILLS; PANEL WANTS SIGNAL AT SCHOOL ENTRANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city traffic commission has recommended placing a traffic signal at the 
entrance to Laguna Hills High School on Paseo de Valencia. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council must approve the installation, which would cost $100,000. The 
council will discuss the recommendation at its Aug. 9 meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 A traffic study showed that more than 420 cars travel along Paseo de Valencia 
in front of Laguna Hills High every hour. At least 140 cars per hour enter or 
exit the high school there. 
</P>
