<HEADLINE>
<P>
MASTER CHORALE OF ORANGE COUNTY OPENS OCT. 15 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Master Chorale of Orange County will team up with the Gay Men's Chorus of 
Los Angeles to open the chorale's 1994-95 season, Oct. 15 at the Orange County 
Performing Arts Center in Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
 The two groups will sing Ned Rorem's "Love Alone" and Brahms' "Alto Rhapsody," 
with soloist Wendy Hillhouse.Billed as an AIDS memorial concert, the program 
will conclude with Faure's Requiem, with soprano Rebecca Semanie and baritone 
Douglas Lawrence as soloists. 
</P>
<P>
 The season will continue with a holiday program Dec. 10 at the Performing Arts 
Center, a Valentine's Day program Feb. 12 at St. Andrew's Presbyterian Church 
in Newport Beach, and Benjamin Britten's "War Requiem," sung during a screening 
of Derek Jarman's "War Requiem" with the late Laurence Olivier, May 20 at the 
Performing Arts Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Season tickets: $44-$120. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (714) 556-6262. 
</P>
