<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE SEEK BROTHER OF ITALY PREMIER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Italian police were seeking the brother of Prime Minister Silvio Berlusconi on 
Wednesday after magistrates ordered his arrest for suspected corruption in the 
latest blow to the battered right-wing government. 
</P>
<P>
 The arrest warrant was issued as prosecutors examined allegations that tax 
examiners were bribed in exchange for approval of doctored books at 
Berlusconi's firm Fininvest. 
</P>
<P>
 The whereabouts of Paolo Berlusconi, who heads the family's property 
businesses, were unknown, but judicial sources speculated he might surrender 
today. 
</P>
<P>
 Paolo Berlusconi already faces trial in two other corruption cases. 
</P>
