WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; SPICE NETWORK FANS MAY REQUIRE FILTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The cable provider for Oxnard, Port Hueneme, El Rio, and some incorporated 
areas of Ventura County announced Wednesday that it has found a way to improve 
the scrambling of the Spice Network, a controversial adult channel. 
</P>
<P>
 Jones Intercable and the network were harshly criticized in March by residents 
and religious leaders who complained that despite scrambling, the audio portion 
of the broadcast, as well as an occasional image, could be heard and seen in 
some homes. 
</P>
<P>
 The cable company plans to block the channel from the transmission point, 
requiring those residents who subscribe to the Spice Network to install small 
filters that allow the channel to come through. 
</P>
<P>
 The filters will not be available until early August. For information, call 
485-7774. MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
