COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: AID FOR MINOR QUAKE REPAIRS IS AVAILABLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Low-income residents of Fillmore, Piru and Simi Valley whose homes suffered 
cosmetic damage in January's earthquake may qualify for free repair work 
through a program announced Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Families with annual incomes falling below the federal poverty level are 
eligible to apply for up to $1,500 worth of minor repairs. 
</P>
<P>
 Repairs covered in the program include replacement of cracked windows and 
doors. 
</P>
<P>
 The program is called the "Community Partnership for Earthquake Repair." 
</P>
