 The project is being funded with $300,000 from Southern California Gas Co., 
the state Department of Economic Opportunity, the Ventura County Commission on 
Human Concerns and the Job Training Policy Council. 
</P>
<P>
 Repairs will be performed by crews employed by the Commission on Human 
Concerns. 
</P>
