SHOWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEPHANIE SIMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Liza Minelli, Willie Nelson, Bill Cosby, Tony Bennett and Ray Charles are 
among the stars who have been lined up to perform at the Thousand Oaks Civic 
Arts Plaza in the year ahead. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets for a dozen of the big-name shows go on sale Monday, with prices 
ranging from $22 to $90. 
</P>
<P>
 In the first marquee show after Broadway star Bernadette Peters performs 
during the grand opening, blues and jazz artist Ray Charles will take the stage 
Oct. 30, backed up by a 40-piece orchestra. 
</P>
<P>
 Comedian Howie Mandell will bring his shtick to the stage Nov. 18, followed 
the next night by singer-songwriter Paul Anka. For a change of pace, country 
music guru Willie Nelson will swing into town Nov. 20. 
</P>
<P>
 To open December, veteran pop and country singer Anne Murray will present two 
shows, followed by Tony Bennett Dec. 4. Actor Bill Cosby will take the stage 
for two performances Dec. 18. 
</P>
<P>
 While agents at Avalon Attractions are still firming up dates for 1995, they 
have announced the following shows, for which tickets will be available 
starting Monday: 
</P>
<P>
 Michael Feinstein will sing classic, sentimental tunes on Feb. 3; Kenny Rogers 
will offer four performances the weekend of Feb. 17-19; Peter, Paul and Mary 
will hit town March 19; Liza Minelli will give five concerts the week of March 
21-25, and Kenny Loggins will sing April 20. Shirley MacLaine is expected to 
perform May 26 and 27. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the box office at 449-ARTS, or TicketMaster at 
583-8700. The temporary box office, located in The Oaks mall across from Mrs. 
Field's Cookies, is open seven days a week during the mall's regular hours. 
STEPHANIE SIMON 
