EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: FREE HOT LINE OFFERS COMMUTE ADVISORIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County commuters who rely on Los Angeles public transit to get to work 
can call a toll-free hot line for updates on the MTA strike and alternate 
routes. 
</P>
<P>
 Public transit in Ventura County has not been affected by the strike. But some 
residents may be affected if they take the bus or train to work once they are 
in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 The number for the hot line, which provides information in English and 
Spanish, is 1-800-COMMUTE. 
</P>
<P>
 The hot line offers updates on MTA bus routes and rail schedules, Metrolink 
schedules and fares, car-pool and van-pool information and Caltrans freeway 
advisories. SARA CATANIA 
