BRIEFLY: TECHNOLOGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chip-Building Alliance Formed: International Business Machines Corp., AT&T 
Corp., Motorola Inc. and Loral Corp. are joining forces to develop a new 
computer chip-making technology based on X-rays instead of ultraviolet 
light.X-rays are expected to allow the production of chips with circuits half 
the width of those found today, making it possible to pack more transistors on 
a chip. This heavyweight alliance comes as companies in the semiconductor 
industry increasingly seek partners to spread the high costs of developing new 
generations of chips, said Ronald Brown, an analyst with Dataquest Inc. The 
alliance will be formally announced in the next several weeks, an IBM 
spokeswoman said. Marketable products are not expected until early next 
century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
