<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 May Department Stores to Buy Shoe Chain: The St. Louis-based retailer, the 
nation's sixth-largest, said its fast-growing Payless ShoeSource subsidiary 
will acquire Columbus, Ohio-based Kobacker Co.Terms of the deal were not 
disclosed. Kobacker, a private retailer, is shedding almost all its assets. Six 
hundred of the 679 Kobacker stores will be remodeled and reopened. Payless, 
which represented $2 billion of May's $11 billion in sales in 1993, will have 
4,600 outlets after the acquisition and expansions in the next year. "The newly 
acquired stores will add significantly to Payless ShoeSource's nationwide 
presence, strengthening our position in a number of major markets," Payless 
Chairman and Chief Executive Dale Hilpert said. 
</P>
