<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 IMF Report Urges Federal Sales Tax: The International Monetary Fund's annual 
report says the United States should consider the tax to reduce its budget 
deficit. The review said that with such a tax, the United States could 
encourage consumers to save more and spend less and could reduce its need for 
foreign investors to finance the deficit through Treasury bond purchases. The 
far-reaching review, covering the year ended April 30, said the IMF's executive 
directors all agreed that the United States should move further to deal with 
its deficit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
