<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: AUTOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sport Utility Vehicles, Trucks Recalled: Isuzu Motors Ltd., American Honda 
Motor Co. and Chrysler Corp. are recalling about 140,200 vehicles. The 
companies said there have been no reports of accidents or injuries related to 
the problems.The Isuzu and Honda recalls affect 133,190 sport utility vehicles. 
The engines have a rubber and metal oil plug that could dislodge and cause 
leaks that might result in engine damage or fire. Affected are Isuzu Rodeos 
from 1992-94, Honda Passport LX and EX models from 1994 and Isuzu Troopers from 
1992-93. The Chrysler recall involves Dodge Ram 1500 and 2500 pickup trucks 
from 1994 that were built without rear bumpers. Federal crash tests of the 
vehicles showed that impact from the rear could cause fuel leaks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
