<P>
 Ford Negotiating Loan With Japan: The auto maker is discussing a $300-million 
loan with the government-controlled Import-Export Bank of Japan to help it 
develop right-hand-drive vehicles for export there, according to the Japanese 
newspaper Nihon Keizai. The action signals Japan's eagerness to narrow its U.S. 
trade surplus and earn good will after resisting Clinton Administration calls 
to guarantee more imports of U.S. cars. The bank officially denied the report, 
but bank sources and a Ford official said they have discussed a loan with an 
interest rate of slightly above 4%. 
